    Asearch
    Allows for searching of a given DirectedGraph with an A* search - by using a comparator in order to give weighting to particular state spaces over one another.
    AsearchNode<E>
    Acts as a node that operates in an A* search.
    CourierDelivery
    Given a list of Jobs with a "start" point and a "finish" point from standard input, this class creates a graph, and adds these points to the graph.
    This class then performs an A* search on the graph to find the minimal spanning path from one "CourierDeliveryJobVector" to another that passes through every "CourierDeliveryJobVector"

    For details on the Heuristic please see the CourierDeliveryHeuristic class

    Depending on the jobs entered, the program could reasonably evaluate up to 19 nodes, or as little as 15 etc, so it should be noted that 17 is a general limit, and not a fixed limit.
    CourierDeliveryHeuristic
    Heuristic takes an object of type E, and provides an arbitrary/relative estimate of how close the particular object is to the goal state.

    This implements Heuristic interface with generic type of "SearchNode"

    This heuristic is both monotonic and admissible.
    CourierDeliveryJobVector
    Provides the class for a "vector" that consists of two points - a "start" point and a "finish" These two pairs of coordinates can be accessed.
